ntus’ crucial place within the inherited epic tradition and his role in shaping the literary and identity politics of Late Antique society.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aEpic poetry, GreekxHistory and criticism. 4aClassics & Ancient History. 7aHISTORY / Ancient / Greece.2bisacsh1 aBarbaresco, Katia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBremmer, Jan N., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBär, Silvio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBär, Silvio, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBärtschi, Arnold, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarvounis, Katerina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFerreccio, Alessia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoldhill, Simon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGreensmith, Emma, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGärtner, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLovato, Valeria F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMaciver, Calum A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMaly-Preuss, Jordan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMiddleton, Fran, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOzbek, Leyla, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRenker, Stephan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aScafoglio, Giampiero, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aScheijnen, Tine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchoess, A. Sophie, 